{"nodes": [{"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom", "label": "North-star 8 \u2014 The Atom: One Compute Block", "file_type": "document", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "What is the smallest learnable unit? The default (dot-product+ReLU) is one option; pick the atom whose math IS capacitor physics \u2014 liquid/ODE/reservoir."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_kan", "label": "Kolmogorov\u2013Arnold Networks (KAN)", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Liu et al. 2024: learn the transfer CURVE on edges (splines), not the gain; analog-friendly (spline = analog curve fitting) for physics-structured tasks; not the Phase-1 atom."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_liquid_ltc", "label": "Liquid Time-Constant Networks", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Hasani et al. 2021: dx/dt = -x/tau(x,I)+f is literally an RC circuit with input-dependent tau \u2014 a leaky cap IS a liquid neuron; 19 neurons drive a car; strongest Phase-2 time-series atom candidate."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_neural_ode", "label": "Neural ODEs", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Chen et al. 2018: depth = integration time, O(1) memory via adjoint; conceptual license that analog charge evolution IS computation."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_capsule", "label": "Capsule Networks", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Sabour/Frosst/Hinton 2017: atom outputs a VECTOR (magnitude=presence, direction=pose) via routing-by-agreement; raises 'should the atom emit a small typed bundle, not a scalar'; routing = analog WTA vote."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_dendritic", "label": "Dendritic computation", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Poirazi & Mel 2003 / Beniaguev 2021: one biological neuron ~ a 2-layer (even 5-8 layer) net; license for a nonlinear-internal atom \u2014 the Ganglion 2-3-3-2 already is one."}, {"id": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_reservoir", "label": "Reservoir computing", "file_type": "concept", "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "source_url": null, "captured_at": null, "author": null, "contributor": null, "rationale": "Jaeger 2001 / Maass 2002: fix random recurrent reservoir, train only linear readout; device mismatch is a FEATURE; cheapest Phase-2 thinking loop candidate \u2014 fixed analog reservoir + SCFF/GD readout."}], "edges": [{"source": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom", "target": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_kan", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"source": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom", "target": "draft6_0_research_north_star_th_8_atom_liquid_ltc", "relation": "references", "confidence": "EXTRACTED", "confidence_score": 1.0, "source_file": "draft6.0\\research\\north-star\\th\\8-atom.md", "source_location": null, "weight": 1.0}, {"sourc